ca.uqac.lif.petitpoucet

Class NodeFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uqac.lif.petitpoucet.NodeFactory

  • public class NodeFactory
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides lineage nodes in a local context. Objects that implement a descendant of the Queryable interface should use a node factory to create nodes, and not call their constructors directly.
    Author:
    Sylvain Hall√©

      • getPartNode

        public PartNode getPartNode(Part p,
                            java.lang.Object subject)
        Gets an instance of PartNode corresponding to a particular part and subject. If the same part and subject are requested multiple times, the factory reuses the same node instance on each successive call.
        Parameters:
        p - The part
        subject - The subject
        Returns:
        The node instance

      • getAndNode

        public AndNode getAndNode()
        Gets an instance of AndNode. A new instance is created on every call to this method. The factory keeps no track of this object after it is returned.
        Returns:
        The and node
